README - Lean SharePoint PDF → Cleaned TXT Pipeline

Overview

This solution converts approved PDFs from a source SharePoint library into cleaned TXT files in a destination library (Cleaned) for use in Copilot Studio.

It is designed to be:

Simple

Consistent

Hard for users to mess up



---

Core Rules (Non-Negotiable)

1. Folder = Category

Each document must live in ONE folder only

Only one level deep

No nested folders


Example:

RawPolicies/
  HR/
  IT/
  Finance/

2. Only Two Metadata Columns in Source

Status (Choice)

Draft

Approved

Archived


Document Type (Choice)

FAQ

Policy

Procedure

Guidance

Form


That’s it. Nothing else.


---

Architecture

Source Library (Raw)

Stores original PDFs

User-managed


Destination Library (Cleaned)

Auto-created by script

Stores cleaned TXT files

Used as Copilot knowledge source



---

Destination Library Schema

Business Metadata

Status (Choice)

DocumentType (Choice)

Category (Text)


Processing Metadata

SourcePath (Text)

OriginalFileName (Text)

NeedsOCR (Yes/No)

ProcessingStatus (Choice)

ProcessedDate (DateTime)

SourceFileUrl (Text)

SourceModifiedDate (DateTime)

Keywords (Multi-line)

KeyPhrases (Multi-line)

SearchTags (Multi-line)

ContentQuality (Choice)



---

Indexed Columns (Important)

Index these in Cleaned:

Status

DocumentType

Category

NeedsOCR

ProcessingStatus

SourceModifiedDate

ContentQuality



---

What the Script Does

For Each File:

1. Reads metadata from source


2. Determines Category from folder


3. Checks Status




---

If Status = Approved

Download PDF

Open in Word

Remove:

Images

Headers/Footers

Page numbers

Repeated lines


Extract clean text

Generate:

Keywords

Key phrases

Search tags


Save as .txt

Upload to Cleaned

Overwrite if already exists

Update metadata



---

If Status ≠ Approved

Delete matching file from Cleaned (if exists)

Skip processing



---

If File Unchanged

Skip processing



---

Reprocessing Logic

Scenario	Action

New + Approved	Create file
Updated + Approved	Reprocess + overwrite
Unchanged + Approved	Skip
No longer Approved	Delete from Cleaned



---

Output File Structure

Each TXT file contains:

[METADATA]
Status: Approved
DocumentType: Policy
Category: HR
...
[/METADATA]

[CONTENT]
Cleaned text...


---

Why This Works Well

No messy taxonomy

No duplicate category logic

Easy for users

Predictable for AI retrieval

Easy to filter in Copilot topics



---

User Instructions (Give Them This)

1. Upload document


2. Put it in the correct folder


3. Set Status


4. Set Document Type



Done.

If they can’t follow that, the system isn’t the problem.


---

Copilot Studio Usage

Use Cleaned library only as knowledge source.

To scope responses:

Point topics to specific folders (categories)


Example:

HR topic → /Cleaned/HR

IT topic → /Cleaned/IT



---

Final Notes

This is intentionally strict.

Loose systems create:

Bad metadata

Bad retrieval

Bad answers


Tight systems create:

Predictable structure

Better AI responses

Less maintenance


Stick to the rules and this will scale cleanly.






